      "body" : "@paraquat &amp; Oskar Lund that is not actually correct. Yes, the code provided will create two arrays, but this <b>approach</b> does not. The problem in this code here is the use of a zero length array as the argument. The <a href=\"http://grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/openjdk/6-b14/java/util/ArrayList.java#ArrayList.toArray%28java.lang.Object%5B%5D%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ArrayList.toArray source code</a> shows that if the contents will fit, the original array will be used. I think in a fair comparison you&#39;ll find this method to be as efficient (if not more) and, of course, less code to maintain."
